119AccessibilityRenderObject::AccessibilityRenderObject(RenderObject* renderer)
120 : AccessibilityNodeObject(renderer->node())
121 , m_renderer(makeWeakPtr(renderer))
122{
123#ifndef NDEBUG
124 m_renderer->setHasAXObject(true);
125#endif
126}
127
128AccessibilityRenderObject::~AccessibilityRenderObject()
129{
130 ASSERT(isDetached());
131}
132
133void AccessibilityRenderObject::init()
134{
135 AccessibilityNodeObject::init();
136}
137
138Ref<AccessibilityRenderObject> AccessibilityRenderObject::create(RenderObject* renderer)
139{
140 return adoptRef(*new AccessibilityRenderObject(renderer));
141}

143void AccessibilityRenderObject::detachRemoteParts(AccessibilityDetachmentType detachmentType)
144{
145 AccessibilityNodeObject::detachRemoteParts(detachmentType);
146
147 detachRemoteSVGRoot();
148
149#ifndef NDEBUG
150 if (m_renderer)
151 m_renderer->setHasAXObject(false);
152#endif
153 m_renderer = nullptr;
154}

156RenderBoxModelObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::renderBoxModelObject() const
157{
158 if (!is<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer()))
159 return nullptr;
160 return downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer());
161}

163void AccessibilityRenderObject::setRenderer(RenderObject* renderer)
164{
165 m_renderer = makeWeakPtr(renderer);
166 setNode(renderer->node());
167}

169static inline bool isInlineWithContinuation(RenderObject& object)
170{
171 return is<RenderInline>(object) && downcast<RenderInline>(object).continuation();
172}
173
174static inline RenderObject* firstChildInContinuation(RenderInline& renderer)
175{
176 auto* continuation = renderer.continuation();
177
178 while (continuation) {
179 if (is<RenderBlock>(*continuation))
180 return continuation;
181 if (RenderObject* child = continuation->firstChild())
182 return child;
183 continuation = downcast<RenderInline>(*continuation).continuation();
184 }
185
186 return nullptr;
187}
188
189static inline RenderObject* firstChildConsideringContinuation(RenderObject& renderer)
190{
191 RenderObject* firstChild = renderer.firstChildSlow();
192
193 // We don't want to include the end of a continuation as the firstChild of the
194 // anonymous parent, because everything has already been linked up via continuation.
195 // CSS first-letter selector is an example of this case.
196 if (renderer.isAnonymous() && is<RenderInline>(firstChild) && downcast<RenderInline>(*firstChild).isContinuation())
197 firstChild = nullptr;
198
199 if (!firstChild && isInlineWithContinuation(renderer))
200 firstChild = firstChildInContinuation(downcast<RenderInline>(renderer));
201
202 return firstChild;
203}
204
205
206static inline RenderObject* lastChildConsideringContinuation(RenderObject& renderer)
207{
208 if (!is<RenderInline>(renderer) && !is<RenderBlock>(renderer))
209 return &renderer;
210
211 RenderObject* lastChild = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer).lastChild();
212 for (auto* current = &downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer); current; ) {
213 if (RenderObject* newLastChild = current->lastChild())
214 lastChild = newLastChild;
215
216 current = current->inlineContinuation();
217 }
218
219 return lastChild;
220}
221
222AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::firstChild() const
223{
224 if (!m_renderer)
225 return nullptr;
226
227 RenderObject* firstChild = firstChildConsideringContinuation(*m_renderer);
228
229 // If an object can't have children, then it is using this method to help
230 // calculate some internal property (like its description).
231 // In this case, it should check the Node level for children in case they're
232 // not rendered (like a <meter> element).
233 if (!firstChild && !canHaveChildren())
234 return AccessibilityNodeObject::firstChild();
235
236 auto objectCache = axObjectCache();
237 return objectCache ? objectCache->getOrCreate(firstChild) : nullptr;
238}
239
240AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::lastChild() const
241{
242 if (!m_renderer)
243 return nullptr;
244
245 RenderObject* lastChild = lastChildConsideringContinuation(*m_renderer);
246
247 if (!lastChild && !canHaveChildren())
248 return AccessibilityNodeObject::lastChild();
249
250 auto objectCache = axObjectCache();
251 return objectCache ? objectCache->getOrCreate(lastChild) : nullptr;
252}
253
254static inline RenderInline* startOfContinuations(RenderObject& renderer)
255{
256 if (!is<RenderElement>(renderer))
257 return nullptr;
258 auto& renderElement = downcast<RenderElement>(renderer);
259 if (is<RenderInline>(renderElement) && renderElement.isContinuation() && is<RenderInline>(renderElement.element()->renderer()))
260 return downcast<RenderInline>(renderer.node()->renderer());
261
262 // Blocks with a previous continuation always have a next continuation
263 if (is<RenderBlock>(renderElement) && downcast<RenderBlock>(renderElement).inlineContinuation())
264 return downcast<RenderInline>(downcast<RenderBlock>(renderElement).inlineContinuation()->element()->renderer());
265
266 return nullptr;
267}
268
269static inline RenderObject* endOfContinuations(RenderObject& renderer)
270{
271 if (!is<RenderInline>(renderer) && !is<RenderBlock>(renderer))
272 return &renderer;
273
274 auto* previous = &downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer);
275 for (auto* current = previous; current; ) {
276 previous = current;
277 current = current->inlineContinuation();
278 }
279
280 return previous;
281}
282
283
284static inline RenderObject* childBeforeConsideringContinuations(RenderInline* renderer, RenderObject* child)
285{
286 RenderObject* previous = nullptr;
287 for (RenderBoxModelObject* currentContainer = renderer; currentContainer; ) {
288 if (is<RenderInline>(*currentContainer)) {
289 auto* current = currentContainer->firstChild();
290 while (current) {
291 if (current == child)
292 return previous;
293 previous = current;
294 current = current->nextSibling();
295 }
296
297 currentContainer = currentContainer->continuation();
298 } else if (is<RenderBlock>(*currentContainer)) {
299 if (currentContainer == child)
300 return previous;
301
302 previous = currentContainer;
303 currentContainer = currentContainer->inlineContinuation();
304 }
305 }
306
307 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
308 return nullptr;
309}
310
311static inline bool firstChildIsInlineContinuation(RenderElement& renderer)
312{
313 RenderObject* child = renderer.firstChild();
314 return is<RenderInline>(child) && downcast<RenderInline>(*child).isContinuation();
315}
316
317AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::previousSibling() const
318{
319 if (!m_renderer)
320 return nullptr;
321
322 RenderObject* previousSibling = nullptr;
323
324 // Case 1: The node is a block and is an inline's continuation. In that case, the inline's
325 // last child is our previous sibling (or further back in the continuation chain)
326 RenderInline* startOfConts;
327 if (is<RenderBox>(*m_renderer) && (startOfConts = startOfContinuations(*m_renderer)))
328 previousSibling = childBeforeConsideringContinuations(startOfConts, renderer());
329
330 // Case 2: Anonymous block parent of the end of a continuation - skip all the way to before
331 // the parent of the start, since everything in between will be linked up via the continuation.
332 else if (m_renderer->isAnonymousBlock() && firstChildIsInlineContinuation(downcast<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer))) {
333 RenderBlock& renderBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer);
334 auto* firstParent = startOfContinuations(*renderBlock.firstChild())->parent();
335 ASSERT(firstParent);
336 while (firstChildIsInlineContinuation(*firstParent))
337 firstParent = startOfContinuations(*firstParent->firstChild())->parent();
338 previousSibling = firstParent->previousSibling();
339 }
340
341 // Case 3: The node has an actual previous sibling
342 else if (RenderObject* ps = m_renderer->previousSibling())
343 previousSibling = ps;
344
345 // Case 4: This node has no previous siblings, but its parent is an inline,
346 // and is another node's inline continutation. Follow the continuation chain.
347 else if (is<RenderInline>(m_renderer->parent()) && (startOfConts = startOfContinuations(*m_renderer->parent())))
348 previousSibling = childBeforeConsideringContinuations(startOfConts, m_renderer->parent()->firstChild());
349
350 if (!previousSibling)
351 return nullptr;
352
353 if (auto* objectCache = axObjectCache())
354 return objectCache->getOrCreate(previousSibling);
355
356 return nullptr;
357}
358
359static inline bool lastChildHasContinuation(RenderElement& renderer)
360{
361 RenderObject* child = renderer.lastChild();
362 return child && isInlineWithContinuation(*child);
363}
364
365AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::nextSibling() const
366{
367 if (!m_renderer || is<RenderView>(*m_renderer))
368 return nullptr;
369
370 RenderObject* nextSibling = nullptr;
371
372 // Case 1: node is a block and has an inline continuation. Next sibling is the inline continuation's
373 // first child.
374 RenderInline* inlineContinuation;
375 if (is<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer) && (inlineContinuation = downcast<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer).inlineContinuation()))
376 nextSibling = firstChildConsideringContinuation(*inlineContinuation);
377
378 // Case 2: Anonymous block parent of the start of a continuation - skip all the way to
379 // after the parent of the end, since everything in between will be linked up via the continuation.
380 else if (m_renderer->isAnonymousBlock() && lastChildHasContinuation(downcast<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer))) {
381 RenderElement* lastParent = endOfContinuations(*downcast<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer).lastChild())->parent();
382 ASSERT(lastParent);
383 while (lastChildHasContinuation(*lastParent))
384 lastParent = endOfContinuations(*lastParent->lastChild())->parent();
385 nextSibling = lastParent->nextSibling();
386 }
387
388 // Case 3: node has an actual next sibling
389 else if (RenderObject* ns = m_renderer->nextSibling())
390 nextSibling = ns;
391
392 // Case 4: node is an inline with a continuation. Next sibling is the next sibling of the end
393 // of the continuation chain.
394 else if (isInlineWithContinuation(*m_renderer))
395 nextSibling = endOfContinuations(*m_renderer)->nextSibling();
396
397 // Case 5: node has no next sibling, and its parent is an inline with a continuation.
398 // Case 5.1: After case 4, (the element was inline w/ continuation but had no sibling), then check it's parent.
399 if (!nextSibling && m_renderer->parent() && isInlineWithContinuation(*m_renderer->parent())) {
400 auto& continuation = *downcast<RenderInline>(*m_renderer->parent()).continuation();
401
402 // Case 5a: continuation is a block - in this case the block itself is the next sibling.
403 if (is<RenderBlock>(continuation))
404 nextSibling = &continuation;
405 // Case 5b: continuation is an inline - in this case the inline's first child is the next sibling
406 else
407 nextSibling = firstChildConsideringContinuation(continuation);
408
409 // After case 4, there are chances that nextSibling has the same node as the current renderer,
410 // which might lead to adding the same child repeatedly.
411 if (nextSibling && nextSibling->node() == m_renderer->node()) {
412 if (AccessibilityObject* nextObj = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(nextSibling))
413 return nextObj->nextSibling();
414 }
415 }
416
417 if (!nextSibling)
418 return nullptr;
419
420 auto* objectCache = axObjectCache();
421 if (!objectCache)
422 return nullptr;
423
424 // Make sure next sibling has the same parent.
425 auto* nextObject = objectCache->getOrCreate(nextSibling);
426 if (nextObject && nextObject->parentObject() != this->parentObject())
427 return nullptr;
428
429 return nextObject;
430}

432static RenderBoxModelObject* nextContinuation(RenderObject& renderer)
433{
434 if (is<RenderInline>(renderer) && !renderer.isReplaced())
435 return downcast<RenderInline>(renderer).continuation();
436 if (is<RenderBlock>(renderer))
437 return downcast<RenderBlock>(renderer).inlineContinuation();
438 return nullptr;
439}
440
441RenderObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::renderParentObject() const
442{
443 if (!m_renderer)
444 return nullptr;
445
446 RenderElement* parent = m_renderer->parent();
447
448 // Case 1: node is a block and is an inline's continuation. Parent
449 // is the start of the continuation chain.
450 RenderInline* startOfConts = nullptr;
451 RenderObject* firstChild = nullptr;
452 if (is<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer) && (startOfConts = startOfContinuations(*m_renderer)))
453 parent = startOfConts;
454
455 // Case 2: node's parent is an inline which is some node's continuation; parent is
456 // the earliest node in the continuation chain.
457 else if (is<RenderInline>(parent) && (startOfConts = startOfContinuations(*parent)))
458 parent = startOfConts;
459
460 // Case 3: The first sibling is the beginning of a continuation chain. Find the origin of that continuation.
461 else if (parent && (firstChild = parent->firstChild()) && firstChild->node()) {
462 // Get the node's renderer and follow that continuation chain until the first child is found
463 RenderObject* nodeRenderFirstChild = firstChild->node()->renderer();
464 while (nodeRenderFirstChild != firstChild) {
465 for (RenderObject* contsTest = nodeRenderFirstChild; contsTest; contsTest = nextContinuation(*contsTest)) {
466 if (contsTest == firstChild) {
467 parent = nodeRenderFirstChild->parent();
468 break;
469 }
470 }
471 RenderObject* parentFirstChild = parent->firstChild();
472 if (firstChild == parentFirstChild)
473 break;
474 firstChild = parentFirstChild;
475 if (!firstChild->node())
476 break;
477 nodeRenderFirstChild = firstChild->node()->renderer();
478 }
479 }
480
481 return parent;
482}

484AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::parentObjectIfExists() const
485{
486 AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache();
487 if (!cache)
488 return nullptr;
489
490 // WebArea's parent should be the scroll view containing it.
491 if (isWebArea())
492 return cache->get(&m_renderer->view().frameView());
493
494 return cache->get(renderParentObject());
495}
496
497AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::parentObject() const
498{
499 if (!m_renderer)
500 return nullptr;
501
502 if (ariaRoleAttribute() == AccessibilityRole::MenuBar)
503 return axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(m_renderer->parent());
504
505 // menuButton and its corresponding menu are DOM siblings, but Accessibility needs them to be parent/child
506 if (ariaRoleAttribute() == AccessibilityRole::Menu) {
507 AccessibilityObject* parent = menuButtonForMenu();
508 if (parent)
509 return parent;
510 }
511
512 AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache();
513 if (!cache)
514 return nullptr;
515
516 RenderObject* parentObj = renderParentObject();
517 if (parentObj)
518 return cache->getOrCreate(parentObj);
519
520 // WebArea's parent should be the scroll view containing it.
521 if (isWebArea())
522 return cache->getOrCreate(&m_renderer->view().frameView());
523
524 return nullptr;
525}

527bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isAttachment() const
528{
529 RenderBoxModelObject* renderer = renderBoxModelObject();
530 if (!renderer)
531 return false;
532 // Widgets are the replaced elements that we represent to AX as attachments
533 bool isWidget = renderer->isWidget();
534
535 return isWidget && ariaRoleAttribute() == AccessibilityRole::Unknown;
536}

538bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isFileUploadButton() const
539{
540 if (m_renderer && is<HTMLInputElement>(m_renderer->node())) {
541 HTMLInputElement& input = downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*m_renderer->node());
542 return input.isFileUpload();
543 }
544
545 return false;
546}
547
548bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isOffScreen() const
549{
550 if (!m_renderer)
551 return true;
552
553 IntRect contentRect = snappedIntRect(m_renderer->absoluteClippedOverflowRectForSpatialNavigation());
554 // FIXME: unclear if we need LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect.
555 IntRect viewRect = m_renderer->view().frameView().visibleContentRect(ScrollableArea::LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect);
556 viewRect.intersect(contentRect);
557 return viewRect.isEmpty();
558}
559
560Element* AccessibilityRenderObject::anchorElement() const
561{
562 if (!m_renderer)
563 return nullptr;
564
565 AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache();
566 if (!cache)
567 return nullptr;
568
569 RenderObject* currentRenderer;
570
571 // Search up the render tree for a RenderObject with a DOM node. Defer to an earlier continuation, though.
572 for (currentRenderer = renderer(); currentRenderer && !currentRenderer->node(); currentRenderer = currentRenderer->parent()) {
573 if (currentRenderer->isAnonymousBlock()) {
574 if (RenderObject* continuation = downcast<RenderBlock>(*currentRenderer).continuation())
575 return cache->getOrCreate(continuation)->anchorElement();
576 }
577 }
578
579 // bail if none found
580 if (!currentRenderer)
581 return nullptr;
582
583 // search up the DOM tree for an anchor element
584 // NOTE: this assumes that any non-image with an anchor is an HTMLAnchorElement
585 for (Node* node = currentRenderer->node(); node; node = node->parentNode()) {
586 if (is<HTMLAnchorElement>(*node) || (node->renderer() && cache->getOrCreate(node->renderer())->isLink()))
587 return downcast<Element>(node);
588 }
589
590 return nullptr;
591}

593String AccessibilityRenderObject::helpText() const
594{
595 if (!m_renderer)
596 return String();
597
598 const AtomString& ariaHelp = getAttribute(aria_helpAttr);
599 if (!ariaHelp.isEmpty())
600 return ariaHelp;
601
602 String describedBy = ariaDescribedByAttribute();
603 if (!describedBy.isEmpty())
604 return describedBy;
605
606 String description = accessibilityDescription();
607 for (RenderObject* ancestor = renderer(); ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->parent()) {
608 if (is<HTMLElement>(ancestor->node())) {
609 HTMLElement& element = downcast<HTMLElement>(*ancestor->node());
610 const AtomString& summary = element.getAttribute(summaryAttr);
611 if (!summary.isEmpty())
612 return summary;
613
614 // The title attribute should be used as help text unless it is already being used as descriptive text.
615 const AtomString& title = element.getAttribute(titleAttr);
616 if (!title.isEmpty() && description != title)
617 return title;
618 }
619
620 // Only take help text from an ancestor element if its a group or an unknown role. If help was
621 // added to those kinds of elements, it is likely it was meant for a child element.
622 if (AccessibilityObject* axObj = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(ancestor)) {
623 if (!axObj->isGroup() && axObj->roleValue() != AccessibilityRole::Unknown)
624 break;
625 }
626 }
627
628 return String();
629}
630
631String AccessibilityRenderObject::textUnderElement(AccessibilityTextUnderElementMode mode) const
632{
633 if (!m_renderer)
634 return String();
635
636 if (is<RenderFileUploadControl>(*m_renderer))
637 return downcast<RenderFileUploadControl>(*m_renderer).buttonValue();
638
639 // Reflect when a content author has explicitly marked a line break.
640 if (m_renderer->isBR())
641 return "\n"_s;
642
643 if (shouldGetTextFromNode(mode))
644 return AccessibilityNodeObject::textUnderElement(mode);
645
646 // We use a text iterator for text objects AND for those cases where we are
647 // explicitly asking for the full text under a given element.
648 if (is<RenderText>(*m_renderer) || mode.childrenInclusion == AccessibilityTextUnderElementMode::TextUnderElementModeIncludeAllChildren) {
649 // If possible, use a text iterator to get the text, so that whitespace
650 // is handled consistently.
651 Document* nodeDocument = nullptr;
652 std::optional<SimpleRange> textRange;
653 if (Node* node = m_renderer->node()) {
654 nodeDocument = &node->document();
655 textRange = makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(*node);
656 } else {
657 // For anonymous blocks, we work around not having a direct node to create a range from
658 // defining one based in the two external positions defining the boundaries of the subtree.
659 RenderObject* firstChildRenderer = m_renderer->firstChildSlow();
660 RenderObject* lastChildRenderer = m_renderer->lastChildSlow();
661 if (firstChildRenderer && firstChildRenderer->node() && lastChildRenderer && lastChildRenderer->node()) {
662 // We define the start and end positions for the range as the ones right before and after
663 // the first and the last nodes in the DOM tree that is wrapped inside the anonymous block.
664 auto& firstNodeInBlock = *firstChildRenderer->node();
665 nodeDocument = &firstNodeInBlock.document();
666 textRange = makeSimpleRange(positionInParentBeforeNode(&firstNodeInBlock), positionInParentAfterNode(lastChildRenderer->node()));
667 }
668 }
669
670 if (nodeDocument && textRange) {
671 if (Frame* frame = nodeDocument->frame()) {
672 // catch stale WebCoreAXObject (see <rdar://problem/3960196>)
673 if (frame->document() != nodeDocument)
674 return String();
675
676 // Renders referenced by accessibility objects could get destroyed, if TextIterator ends up triggering
677 // style update/layout here. See also AXObjectCache::deferTextChangedIfNeeded().
678 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!nodeDocument->childNeedsStyleRecalc());
679 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!nodeDocument->view()->layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout());
680 return plainText(*textRange, textIteratorBehaviorForTextRange());
681 }
682 }
683
684 // Sometimes text fragments don't have Nodes associated with them (like when
685 // CSS content is used to insert text or when a RenderCounter is used.)
686 if (is<RenderText>(*m_renderer)) {
687 RenderText& renderTextObject = downcast<RenderText>(*m_renderer);
688 if (is<RenderTextFragment>(renderTextObject)) {
689 RenderTextFragment& renderTextFragment = downcast<RenderTextFragment>(renderTextObject);
690 // The alt attribute may be set on a text fragment through CSS, which should be honored.
691 const String& altText = renderTextFragment.altText();
692 if (!altText.isEmpty())
693 return altText;
694 return renderTextFragment.contentString();
695 }
696
697 return renderTextObject.text();
698 }
699 }
700
701 return AccessibilityNodeObject::textUnderElement(mode);
702}
703
704bool AccessibilityRenderObject::shouldGetTextFromNode(AccessibilityTextUnderElementMode mode) const
705{
706 if (!m_renderer)
707 return false;
708
709 // AccessibilityRenderObject::textUnderElement() gets the text of anonymous blocks by using
710 // the child nodes to define positions. CSS tables and their anonymous descendants lack
711 // children with nodes.
712 if (m_renderer->isAnonymous() && m_renderer->isTablePart())
713 return mode.childrenInclusion == AccessibilityTextUnderElementMode::TextUnderElementModeIncludeAllChildren;
714
715 // AccessibilityRenderObject::textUnderElement() calls rangeOfContents() to create the text
716 // range. rangeOfContents() does not include CSS-generated content.
717 if (m_renderer->isBeforeOrAfterContent())
718 return true;
719 if (Node* node = m_renderer->node()) {
720 Node* firstChild = node->pseudoAwareFirstChild();
721 Node* lastChild = node->pseudoAwareLastChild();
722 if ((firstChild && firstChild->isPseudoElement()) || (lastChild && lastChild->isPseudoElement()))
723 return true;
724 }
725
726 return false;
727}
728
729Node* AccessibilityRenderObject::node() const
730{
731 if (!m_renderer)
732 return nullptr;
733 if (m_renderer->isRenderView())
734 return &m_renderer->document();
735 return m_renderer->node();
736}
737
738String AccessibilityRenderObject::stringValue() const
739{
740 if (!m_renderer)
741 return String();
742
743 if (isPasswordField())
744 return passwordFieldValue();
745
746 RenderBoxModelObject* cssBox = renderBoxModelObject();
747
748 if (isARIAStaticText()) {
749 String staticText = text();
750 if (!staticText.length())
751 staticText = textUnderElement();
752 return staticText;
753 }
754
755 if (is<RenderText>(*m_renderer))
756 return textUnderElement();
757
758 if (is<RenderMenuList>(cssBox)) {
759 // RenderMenuList will go straight to the text() of its selected item.
760 // This has to be overridden in the case where the selected item has an ARIA label.
761 HTMLSelectElement& selectElement = downcast<HTMLSelectElement>(*m_renderer->node());
762 int selectedIndex = selectElement.selectedIndex();
763 const Vector<HTMLElement*>& listItems = selectElement.listItems();
764 if (selectedIndex >= 0 && static_cast<size_t>(selectedIndex) < listItems.size()) {
765 const AtomString& overriddenDescription = listItems[selectedIndex]->attributeWithoutSynchronization(aria_labelAttr);
766 if (!overriddenDescription.isNull())
767 return overriddenDescription;
768 }
769 return downcast<RenderMenuList>(*m_renderer).text();
770 }
771
772 if (is<RenderListMarker>(*m_renderer))
773 return downcast<RenderListMarker>(*m_renderer).textWithoutSuffix().toString();
774
775 if (isWebArea())
776 return String();
777
778 if (isTextControl())
779 return text();
780
781#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
782 if (isInputTypePopupButton())
783 return textUnderElement();
784#endif
785
786 if (is<RenderFileUploadControl>(*m_renderer))
787 return downcast<RenderFileUploadControl>(*m_renderer).fileTextValue();
788
789 // FIXME: We might need to implement a value here for more types
790 // FIXME: It would be better not to advertise a value at all for the types for which we don't implement one;
791 // this would require subclassing or making accessibilityAttributeNames do something other than return a
792 // single static array.
793 return String();
794}
795
796bool AccessibilityRenderObject::canHavePlainText() const
797{
798 return isARIAStaticText() || is<RenderText>(*m_renderer) || isTextControl();
799}
800
801HTMLLabelElement* AccessibilityRenderObject::labelElementContainer() const
802{
803 if (!m_renderer)
804 return nullptr;
805
806 // the control element should not be considered part of the label
807 if (isControl())
808 return nullptr;
809
810 // find if this has a parent that is a label
811 for (Node* parentNode = m_renderer->node(); parentNode; parentNode = parentNode->parentNode()) {
812 if (is<HTMLLabelElement>(*parentNode))
813 return downcast<HTMLLabelElement>(parentNode);
814 }
815
816 return nullptr;
817}

819// The boundingBox for elements within the remote SVG element needs to be offset by its position
820// within the parent page, otherwise they are in relative coordinates only.
821void AccessibilityRenderObject::offsetBoundingBoxForRemoteSVGElement(LayoutRect& rect) const
822{
823 for (AccessibilityObject* parent = parentObject(); parent; parent = parent->parentObject()) {
824 if (parent->isAccessibilitySVGRoot()) {
825 rect.moveBy(parent->parentObject()->boundingBoxRect().location());
826 break;
827 }
828 }
829}
830
831LayoutRect AccessibilityRenderObject::boundingBoxRect() const
832{
833 RenderObject* obj = renderer();
834
835 if (!obj)
836 return LayoutRect();
837
838 if (obj->node()) // If we are a continuation, we want to make sure to use the primary renderer.
839 obj = obj->node()->renderer();
840
841 // absoluteFocusRingQuads will query the hierarchy below this element, which for large webpages can be very slow.
842 // For a web area, which will have the most elements of any element, absoluteQuads should be used.
843 // We should also use absoluteQuads for SVG elements, otherwise transforms won't be applied.
844 Vector<FloatQuad> quads;
845 bool isSVGRoot = false;
846
847 if (obj->isSVGRoot())
848 isSVGRoot = true;
849
850 if (is<RenderText>(*obj))
851 quads = downcast<RenderText>(*obj).absoluteQuadsClippedToEllipsis();
852 else if (isWebArea() || isSVGRoot)
853 obj->absoluteQuads(quads);
854 else
855 obj->absoluteFocusRingQuads(quads);
856
857 LayoutRect result = boundingBoxForQuads(obj, quads);
858
859 Document* document = this->document();
860 if (document && document->isSVGDocument())
861 offsetBoundingBoxForRemoteSVGElement(result);
862
863 // The size of the web area should be the content size, not the clipped size.
864 if (isWebArea())
865 result.setSize(obj->view().frameView().contentsSize());
866
867 return result;
868}
869
870LayoutRect AccessibilityRenderObject::checkboxOrRadioRect() const
871{
872 if (!m_renderer)
873 return LayoutRect();
874
875 HTMLLabelElement* label = labelForElement(downcast<Element>(m_renderer->node()));
876 if (!label || !label->renderer())
877 return boundingBoxRect();
878
879 LayoutRect labelRect = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(label)->elementRect();
880 labelRect.unite(boundingBoxRect());
881 return labelRect;
882}
883
884LayoutRect AccessibilityRenderObject::elementRect() const
885{
886 // a checkbox or radio button should encompass its label
887 if (isCheckboxOrRadio())
888 return checkboxOrRadioRect();
889
890 return boundingBoxRect();
891}

893bool AccessibilityRenderObject::supportsPath() const
894{
895 return is<RenderText>(renderer()) || is<RenderSVGShape>(renderer());

897
898Path AccessibilityRenderObject::elementPath() const
899{
900 if (is<RenderText>(renderer())) {
901 Vector<IntRect> rects;
902 downcast<RenderText>(*m_renderer).absoluteRects(rects, flooredLayoutPoint(m_renderer->localToAbsolute()));
903 // If only 1 rect, don't compute path since the bounding rect will be good enough.
904 if (rects.size() < 2)
905 return Path();
906
907 // Compute the path only if this is the last part of a line followed by the beginning of the next line.
908 const auto& style = m_renderer->style();
909 bool rightToLeftText = style.direction() == TextDirection::RTL;
910 static const int xTolerance = 5;
911 static const int yTolerance = 5;
912 bool needsPath = false;
913 IntRect unionRect = rects[0];
914 for (size_t i = 1; i < rects.size(); ++i) {
915 needsPath = abs(rects[i].y() - unionRect.maxY()) < yTolerance // This rect is in a new line.
916 && (rightToLeftText ? rects[i].x() - unionRect.x() > xTolerance
917 : unionRect.x() - rects[i].x() > xTolerance); // And this rect is to right/left of all previous rects.
918
919 if (needsPath)
920 break;
921
922 unionRect.unite(rects[i]);
923 }
924 if (!needsPath)
925 return Path();
926
927 float outlineOffset = style.outlineOffset();
928 float deviceScaleFactor = m_renderer->document().deviceScaleFactor();
929 Vector<FloatRect> pixelSnappedRects;
930 for (auto rect : rects) {
931 rect.inflate(outlineOffset);
932 pixelSnappedRects.append(snapRectToDevicePixels(rect, deviceScaleFactor));
933 }
934
935 return PathUtilities::pathWithShrinkWrappedRects(pixelSnappedRects, 0);
936 }
937
938 if (is<RenderSVGShape>(renderer()) && downcast<RenderSVGShape>(*m_renderer).hasPath()) {
939 Path path = downcast<RenderSVGShape>(*m_renderer).path();
940
941 // The SVG path is in terms of the parent's bounding box. The path needs to be offset to frame coordinates.
942 if (auto svgRoot = ancestorsOfType<RenderSVGRoot>(*m_renderer).first()) {
943 LayoutPoint parentOffset = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(&*svgRoot)->elementRect().location();
944 path.transform(AffineTransform().translate(parentOffset.x(), parentOffset.y()));
945 }
946
947 return path;
948 }
949
950 return Path();
951}
952
953IntPoint AccessibilityRenderObject::linkClickPoint()
954{
955 ASSERT(isLink());
956 /* A link bounding rect can contain points that are not part of the link.
957 For instance, a link that starts at the end of a line and finishes at the
958 beginning of the next line will have a bounding rect that includes the
959 entire two lines. In such a case, the middle point of the bounding rect
960 may not belong to the link element and thus may not activate the link.
961 Hence, return the middle point of the first character in the link if exists.
962 */
963 if (auto range = elementRange()) {
964 auto start = VisiblePosition { makeContainerOffsetPosition(range->start) };
965 auto end = nextVisiblePosition(start);
966 if (contains<ComposedTree>(*range, makeBoundaryPoint(end)))
967 return { boundsForRange(*makeSimpleRange(start, end)).center() };
968 }
969 return AccessibilityObject::clickPoint();
970}
971
972IntPoint AccessibilityRenderObject::clickPoint()
973{
974 // Headings are usually much wider than their textual content. If the mid point is used, often it can be wrong.
975 if (isHeading() && children().size() == 1)
976 return children().first()->clickPoint();
977
978 if (isLink())
979 return linkClickPoint();
980
981 // use the default position unless this is an editable web area, in which case we use the selection bounds.
982 if (!isWebArea() || !canSetValueAttribute())
983 return AccessibilityObject::clickPoint();
984
985 return boundsForVisiblePositionRange(selection()).center();
986}
987
988AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::internalLinkElement() const
989{
990 auto element = anchorElement();
991
992 // Right now, we do not support ARIA links as internal link elements
993 if (!is<HTMLAnchorElement>(element))
994 return nullptr;
995 auto& anchor = downcast<HTMLAnchorElement>(*element);
996
997 auto linkURL = anchor.href();
998 auto fragmentIdentifier = linkURL.fragmentIdentifier();
999 if (fragmentIdentifier.isEmpty())
1000 return nullptr;
1001
1002 // check if URL is the same as current URL
1003 auto documentURL = m_renderer->document().url();
1004 if (!equalIgnoringFragmentIdentifier(documentURL, linkURL))
1005 return nullptr;
1006
1007 auto linkedNode = m_renderer->document().findAnchor(fragmentIdentifier);
1008 if (!linkedNode)
1009 return nullptr;
1010
1011 // The element we find may not be accessible, so find the first accessible object.
1012 return firstAccessibleObjectFromNode(linkedNode);
1013}

1015OptionSet<SpeakAs> AccessibilityRenderObject::speakAsProperty() const

1017 if (!m_renderer)
1018 return AccessibilityObject::speakAsProperty();
1019
1020 return m_renderer->style().speakAs();

1023void AccessibilityRenderObject::addRadioButtonGroupChildren(AXCoreObject* parent, AccessibilityChildrenVector& linkedUIElements) const
1024{
1025 for (const auto& child : parent->children()) {
1026 if (child->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::RadioButton)
1027 linkedUIElements.append(child);
1028 else
1029 addRadioButtonGroupChildren(child.get(), linkedUIElements);
1030 }
1031}
1032
1033void AccessibilityRenderObject::addRadioButtonGroupMembers(AccessibilityChildrenVector& linkedUIElements) const
1034{
1035 if (roleValue() != AccessibilityRole::RadioButton)
1036 return;
1037
1038 Node* node = this->node();
1039 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(node)) {
1040 HTMLInputElement& input = downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*node);
1041 for (auto& radioSibling : input.radioButtonGroup()) {
1042 if (AccessibilityObject* object = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(radioSibling.ptr()))
1043 linkedUIElements.append(object);
1044 }
1045 } else {
1046 // If we didn't find any radio button siblings with the traditional naming, lets search for a radio group role and find its children.
1047 for (AccessibilityObject* parent = parentObject(); parent; parent = parent->parentObject()) {
1048 if (parent->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::RadioGroup)
1049 addRadioButtonGroupChildren(parent, linkedUIElements);
1050 }
1051 }
1052}
1053
1054// linked ui elements could be all the related radio buttons in a group
1055// or an internal anchor connection
1056void AccessibilityRenderObject::linkedUIElements(AccessibilityChildrenVector& linkedUIElements) const
1057{
1058 ariaFlowToElements(linkedUIElements);
1059
1060 if (isLink()) {
1061 AccessibilityObject* linkedAXElement = internalLinkElement();
1062 if (linkedAXElement)
1063 linkedUIElements.append(linkedAXElement);
1064 }
1065
1066 if (roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::RadioButton)
1067 addRadioButtonGroupMembers(linkedUIElements);
1068}

1081 return (this == &object) ? !equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(object.popupValue(), "false")

1106
1107Vector<String> AccessibilityRenderObject::determineDropEffects() const
1108{
1109 // Order is aria-dropeffect, dropzone, webkitdropzone
1110 const AtomString& dropEffects = getAttribute(aria_dropeffectAttr);
1111 if (!dropEffects.isEmpty()) {
1112 String dropEffectsString = dropEffects.string();
1113 dropEffectsString.replace('\n', ' ');
1114 return dropEffectsString.split(' ');
1115 }
1116
1117 auto dropzone = getAttribute(dropzoneAttr);
1118 if (!dropzone.isEmpty())
1119 return Vector<String> { dropzone };
1120
1121 auto webkitdropzone = getAttribute(webkitdropzoneAttr);
1122 if (!webkitdropzone.isEmpty())
1123 return Vector<String> { webkitdropzone };
1124
1125 return { };
1126}
1127
1128bool AccessibilityRenderObject::exposesTitleUIElement() const
1129{
1130 if (!isControl() && !isFigureElement())
1131 return false;
1132
1133 // If this control is ignored (because it's invisible),
1134 // then the label needs to be exposed so it can be visible to accessibility.
1135 if (accessibilityIsIgnored())
1136 return true;
1137
1138 // When controls have their own descriptions, the title element should be ignored.
1139 if (hasTextAlternative())
1140 return false;
1141
1142 // When <label> element has aria-label or aria-labelledby on it, we shouldn't expose it as the
1143 // titleUIElement, otherwise its inner text will be announced by a screenreader.
1144 if (isLabelable()) {
1145 if (HTMLLabelElement* label = labelForElement(downcast<Element>(node()))) {
1146 if (!label->attributeWithoutSynchronization(aria_labelAttr).isEmpty())
1147 return false;
1148 if (AccessibilityObject* labelObject = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(label)) {
1149 if (!labelObject->ariaLabeledByAttribute().isEmpty())
1150 return false;
1151 // To simplify instances where the labeling element includes widget descendants
1152 // which it does not label.
1153 if (is<AccessibilityLabel>(*labelObject)
1154 && downcast<AccessibilityLabel>(*labelObject).containsUnrelatedControls())
1155 return false;
1156 }
1157 }
1158 }
1159
1160 return true;
1161}

1215AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::titleUIElement() const
1216{
1217 if (!m_renderer || !exposesTitleUIElement())
1218 return nullptr;
1219
1220 // if isFieldset is true, the renderer is guaranteed to be a RenderFieldset
1221 if (isFieldset())
1222 return axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(downcast<RenderBlock>(*m_renderer).findFieldsetLegend(RenderBlock::FieldsetIncludeFloatingOrOutOfFlow));
1223
1224 if (isFigureElement())
1225 return captionForFigure();
1226
1227 Node* node = m_renderer->node();
1228 if (!is<Element>(node))
1229 return nullptr;
1230 HTMLLabelElement* label = labelForElement(downcast<Element>(node));
1231 if (label && label->renderer())
1232 return axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(label);
1233
1234 return nullptr;
1235}
1236
1237bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isAllowedChildOfTree() const
1238{
1239 // Determine if this is in a tree. If so, we apply special behavior to make it work like an AXOutline.
1240 AccessibilityObject* axObj = parentObject();
1241 bool isInTree = false;
1242 bool isTreeItemDescendant = false;
1243 while (axObj) {
1244 if (axObj->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::TreeItem)
1245 isTreeItemDescendant = true;
1246 if (axObj->isTree()) {
1247 isInTree = true;
1248 break;
1249 }
1250 axObj = axObj->parentObject();
1251 }
1252
1253 // If the object is in a tree, only tree items should be exposed (and the children of tree items).
1254 if (isInTree) {
1255 AccessibilityRole role = roleValue();
1256 if (role != AccessibilityRole::TreeItem && role != AccessibilityRole::StaticText && !isTreeItemDescendant)
1257 return false;
1258 }
1259 return true;
1260}
1261
1262static AccessibilityObjectInclusion objectInclusionFromAltText(const String& altText)
1263{
1264 // Don't ignore an image that has an alt tag.
1265 if (!altText.isAllSpecialCharacters<isHTMLSpace>())
1266 return AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IncludeObject;
1267
1268 // The informal standard is to ignore images with zero-length alt strings:
1269 // https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/images/decorative/.
1270 if (!altText.isNull())
1271 return AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IgnoreObject;
1272
1273 return AccessibilityObjectInclusion::DefaultBehavior;
1274}
1275
1276AccessibilityObjectInclusion AccessibilityRenderObject::defaultObjectInclusion() const
1277{
1278 // The following cases can apply to any element that's a subclass of AccessibilityRenderObject.
1279
1280 if (!m_renderer)
1281 return AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IgnoreObject;
1282
1283 if (m_renderer->style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible) {
1284 // aria-hidden is meant to override visibility as the determinant in AX hierarchy inclusion.
1285 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(getAttribute(aria_hiddenAttr), "false"))
1286 return AccessibilityObjectInclusion::DefaultBehavior;
1287
1288 return AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IgnoreObject;
1289 }
1290
1291 return AccessibilityObject::defaultObjectInclusion();
1292}
1293
1294static bool webAreaIsPresentational(RenderObject* renderer)
1295{
1296 if (!renderer || !is<RenderView>(*renderer))
1297 return false;
1298
1299 if (auto ownerElement = renderer->document().ownerElement())
1300 return nodeHasPresentationRole(ownerElement);
1301
1302 return false;
1303}
1304
1305bool AccessibilityRenderObject::computeAccessibilityIsIgnored() const
1306{
1307 AXTRACE("AccessibilityRenderObject::computeAccessibilityIsIgnored");
1308#ifndef NDEBUG
1309 ASSERT(m_initialized);
1310#endif
1311
1312 if (!m_renderer)
1313 return true;
1314
1315 // Check first if any of the common reasons cause this element to be ignored.
1316 // Then process other use cases that need to be applied to all the various roles
1317 // that AccessibilityRenderObjects take on.
1318 AccessibilityObjectInclusion decision = defaultObjectInclusion();
1319 if (decision == AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IncludeObject)
1320 return false;
1321 if (decision == AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IgnoreObject)
1322 return true;
1323
1324 // If this element is within a parent that cannot have children, it should not be exposed.
1325 if (isDescendantOfBarrenParent())
1326 return true;
1327
1328 if (roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::Ignored)
1329 return true;
1330
1331 if (roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::Presentational || inheritsPresentationalRole())
1332 return true;
1333
1334 // WebAreas should be ignored if their iframe container is marked as presentational.
1335 if (webAreaIsPresentational(renderer()))
1336 return true;
1337
1338 // An ARIA tree can only have tree items and static text as children.
1339 if (!isAllowedChildOfTree())
1340 return true;
1341
1342 // Allow the platform to decide if the attachment is ignored or not.
1343 if (isAttachment())
1344 return accessibilityIgnoreAttachment();
1345
1346 // ignore popup menu items because AppKit does
1347 if (m_renderer && ancestorsOfType<RenderMenuList>(*m_renderer).first())
1348 return true;
1349
1350 // https://webkit.org/b/161276 Getting the controlObject might cause the m_renderer to be nullptr.
1351 if (!m_renderer)
1352 return true;
1353
1354 if (m_renderer->isBR())
1355 return true;
1356
1357 if (is<RenderText>(*m_renderer)) {
1358 // static text beneath MenuItems and MenuButtons are just reported along with the menu item, so it's ignored on an individual level
1359 AXCoreObject* parent = parentObjectUnignored();
1360 if (parent && (parent->isMenuItem() || parent->ariaRoleAttribute() == AccessibilityRole::MenuButton))
1361 return true;
1362 auto& renderText = downcast<RenderText>(*m_renderer);
1363 if (!renderText.hasRenderedText())
1364 return true;
1365
1366 if (renderText.parent()->isFirstLetter())
1367 return true;
1368
1369 // static text beneath TextControls is reported along with the text control text so it's ignored.
1370 for (AccessibilityObject* parent = parentObject(); parent; parent = parent->parentObject()) {
1371 if (parent->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::TextField)
1372 return true;
1373 }
1374
1375 // Walking up the parent chain might reset the m_renderer.
1376 if (!m_renderer)
1377 return true;
1378
1379 // The alt attribute may be set on a text fragment through CSS, which should be honored.
1380 if (is<RenderTextFragment>(renderText)) {
1381 AccessibilityObjectInclusion altTextInclusion = objectInclusionFromAltText(downcast<RenderTextFragment>(renderText).altText());
1382 if (altTextInclusion == AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IgnoreObject)
1383 return true;
1384 if (altTextInclusion == AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IncludeObject)
1385 return false;
1386 }
1387
1388 // text elements that are just empty whitespace should not be returned
1389 return renderText.text().isAllSpecialCharacters<isHTMLSpace>();
1390 }
1391
1392 if (isHeading())
1393 return false;
1394
1395 if (isLink())
1396 return false;
1397
1398 if (isLandmark())
1399 return false;
1400
1401 // all controls are accessible
1402 if (isControl())
1403 return false;
1404
1405 if (isFigureElement())
1406 return false;
1407
1408 switch (roleValue()) {
1409 case AccessibilityRole::Audio:
1410 case AccessibilityRole::DescriptionListTerm:
1411 case AccessibilityRole::DescriptionListDetail:
1412 case AccessibilityRole::Details:
1413 case AccessibilityRole::DocumentArticle:
1414 case AccessibilityRole::Footer:
1415 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkRegion:
1416 case AccessibilityRole::ListItem:
1417 case AccessibilityRole::Time:
1418 case AccessibilityRole::Video:
1419 return false;
1420 default:
1421 break;
1422 }
1423
1424 if (isImage()) {
1425 // If the image can take focus, it should not be ignored, lest the user not be able to interact with something important.
1426 if (canSetFocusAttribute())
1427 return false;
1428
1429 // First check the RenderImage's altText (which can be set through a style sheet, or come from the Element).
1430 // However, if this is not a native image, fallback to the attribute on the Element.
1431 AccessibilityObjectInclusion altTextInclusion = AccessibilityObjectInclusion::DefaultBehavior;
1432 bool isRenderImage = is<RenderImage>(renderer());
1433 if (isRenderImage)
1434 altTextInclusion = objectInclusionFromAltText(downcast<RenderImage>(*m_renderer).altText());
1435 else
1436 altTextInclusion = objectInclusionFromAltText(getAttribute(altAttr).string());
1437
1438 if (altTextInclusion == AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IgnoreObject)
1439 return true;
1440 if (altTextInclusion == AccessibilityObjectInclusion::IncludeObject)
1441 return false;
1442
1443 // If an image has the title or label attributes, accessibility should be lenient and allow it to appear in the hierarchy (according to WAI-ARIA).
1444 if (!getAttribute(titleAttr).isEmpty() || !getAttribute(aria_labelAttr).isEmpty())
1445 return false;
1446
1447 if (isRenderImage) {
1448 // check for one-dimensional image
1449 RenderImage& image = downcast<RenderImage>(*m_renderer);
1450 if (image.height() <= 1 || image.width() <= 1)
1451 return true;
1452
1453 // check whether rendered image was stretched from one-dimensional file image
1454 if (image.cachedImage()) {
1455 LayoutSize imageSize = image.cachedImage()->imageSizeForRenderer(&image, image.view().zoomFactor());
1456 return imageSize.height() <= 1 || imageSize.width() <= 1;
1457 }
1458 }
1459 return false;
1460 }
1461
1462 if (ariaRoleAttribute() != AccessibilityRole::Unknown)
1463 return false;
1464
1465 if (roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::HorizontalRule)
1466 return false;
1467
1468 // don't ignore labels, because they serve as TitleUIElements
1469 Node* node = m_renderer->node();
1470 if (is<HTMLLabelElement>(node))
1471 return false;
1472
1473 // Anything that is content editable should not be ignored.
1474 // However, one cannot just call node->hasEditableStyle() since that will ask if its parents
1475 // are also editable. Only the top level content editable region should be exposed.
1476 if (hasContentEditableAttributeSet())
1477 return false;
1478
1479 // if this element has aria attributes on it, it should not be ignored.
1480 if (supportsARIAAttributes())
1481 return false;
1482
1483#if ENABLE(MATHML)
1484 // First check if this is a special case within the math tree that needs to be ignored.
1485 if (isIgnoredElementWithinMathTree())
1486 return true;
1487 // Otherwise all other math elements are in the tree.
1488 if (isMathElement())
1489 return false;
1490#endif
1491
1492 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(*m_renderer) && m_renderer->childrenInline() && !canSetFocusAttribute())
1493 return !downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*m_renderer).hasLines() && !mouseButtonListener();
1494
1495 if (isCanvas()) {
1496 if (canvasHasFallbackContent())
1497 return false;
1498
1499 if (is<RenderBox>(*m_renderer)) {
1500 auto& canvasBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*m_renderer);
1501 if (canvasBox.height() <= 1 || canvasBox.width() <= 1)
1502 return true;
1503 }
1504 // Otherwise fall through; use presence of help text, title, or description to decide.
1505 }
1506
1507 if (m_renderer->isListMarker()) {
1508 AXCoreObject* parent = parentObjectUnignored();
1509 return parent && !parent->isListItem();
1510 }
1511
1512 if (isWebArea())
1513 return false;
1514
1515 // The render tree of meter includes a RenderBlock (meter) and a RenderMeter (div).
1516 // We expose the latter and thus should ignore the former. However, if the author
1517 // includes a title attribute on the element, hasAttributesRequiredForInclusion()
1518 // will return true, potentially resulting in a redundant accessible object.
1519 if (is<HTMLMeterElement>(node))
1520 return true;
1521
1522 // Using the presence of an accessible name to decide an element's visibility is not
1523 // as definitive as previous checks, so this should remain as one of the last.
1524 if (hasAttributesRequiredForInclusion())
1525 return false;
1526
1527 // Don't ignore generic focusable elements like <div tabindex=0>
1528 // unless they're completely empty, with no children.
1529 if (isGenericFocusableElement() && node->firstChild())
1530 return false;
1531
1532 // <span> tags are inline tags and not meant to convey information if they have no other aria
1533 // information on them. If we don't ignore them, they may emit signals expected to come from
1534 // their parent. In addition, because included spans are AccessibilityRole::Group objects, and AccessibilityRole::Group
1535 // objects are often containers with meaningful information, the inclusion of a span can have
1536 // the side effect of causing the immediate parent accessible to be ignored. This is especially
1537 // problematic for platforms which have distinct roles for textual block elements.
1538 if (node && node->hasTagName(spanTag))
1539 return true;
1540
1541 // Other non-ignored host language elements
1542 if (node && node->hasTagName(dfnTag))
1543 return false;
1544
1545 if (isStyleFormatGroup())
1546 return false;
1547
1548 // Make sure that ruby containers are not ignored.
1549 if (m_renderer->isRubyRun() || m_renderer->isRubyBlock() || m_renderer->isRubyInline())
1550 return false;
1551
1552 // Find out if this element is inside of a label element.
1553 // If so, it may be ignored because it's the label for a checkbox or radio button.
1554 auto* controlObject = correspondingControlForLabelElement();
1555 if (controlObject && controlObject->isCheckboxOrRadio() && !controlObject->titleUIElement())
1556 return true;
1557
1558 // By default, objects should be ignored so that the AX hierarchy is not
1559 // filled with unnecessary items.
1560 return true;
1561}

1604PlainTextRange AccessibilityRenderObject::documentBasedSelectedTextRange() const
1605{
1606 Node* node = m_renderer->node();
1607 if (!node)
1608 return PlainTextRange();
1609
1610 auto visibleSelection = selection();
1611 auto selectionRange = visibleSelection.firstRange();
1612 if (!selectionRange || !intersects<ComposedTree>(*selectionRange, *node))
1613 return PlainTextRange();
1614
1615 int start = indexForVisiblePosition(visibleSelection.start());
1616 int end = indexForVisiblePosition(visibleSelection.end());
1617 return PlainTextRange(start, end - start);
1618}

1668int AccessibilityRenderObject::insertionPointLineNumber() const
1669{
1670 ASSERT(isTextControl());
1671
1672 // Use the text control native range if it's a native object.
1673 if (isNativeTextControl()) {
1674 auto& textControl = downcast<RenderTextControl>(*m_renderer).textFormControlElement();
1675 int start = textControl.selectionStart();
1676 int end = textControl.selectionEnd();
1677
1678 // If the selection range is not a collapsed range, we don't know whether the insertion point is the start or the end, thus return -1.
1679 // FIXME: for non-collapsed selection, determine the insertion point based on the TextFieldSelectionDirection.
1680 if (start != end)
1681 return -1;
1682
1683 return lineForPosition(textControl.visiblePositionForIndex(start));
1684 }
1685
1686 auto* frame = this->frame();
1687 if (!frame)
1688 return -1;
1689
1690 auto selectedTextRange = frame->selection().selection().firstRange();
1691 // If the selection range is not a collapsed range, we don't know whether the insertion point is the start or the end, thus return -1.
1692 if (!selectedTextRange || !selectedTextRange->collapsed())
1693 return -1;
1694
1695 return lineForPosition(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(selectedTextRange->start));
1696}

1698static void setTextSelectionIntent(AXObjectCache* cache, AXTextStateChangeType type)
1699{
1700 if (!cache)
1701 return;
1702 AXTextStateChangeIntent intent(type, AXTextSelection { AXTextSelectionDirectionDiscontiguous, AXTextSelectionGranularityUnknown, false });
1703 cache->setTextSelectionIntent(intent);
1704 cache->setIsSynchronizingSelection(true);
1705}
1706
1707static void clearTextSelectionIntent(AXObjectCache* cache)
1708{
1709 if (!cache)
1710 return;
1711 cache->setTextSelectionIntent(AXTextStateChangeIntent());
1712 cache->setIsSynchronizingSelection(false);
1713}
1714
1715void AccessibilityRenderObject::setSelectedTextRange(const PlainTextRange& range)
1716{
1717 setTextSelectionIntent(axObjectCache(), range.length ? AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionExtend : AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionMove);
1718
1719 if (isNativeTextControl()) {
1720 HTMLTextFormControlElement& textControl = downcast<RenderTextControl>(*m_renderer).textFormControlElement();
1721 textControl.setSelectionRange(range.start, range.start + range.length);
1722 } else {
1723 ASSERT(node());
1724 auto& node = *this->node();
1725 auto elementRange = this->elementRange();
1726 auto start = visiblePositionForIndexUsingCharacterIterator(node, range.start);
1727 if (!contains<ComposedTree>(*elementRange, makeBoundaryPoint(start)))
1728 start = makeContainerOffsetPosition(elementRange->start);
1729 auto end = visiblePositionForIndexUsingCharacterIterator(node, range.start + range.length);
1730 if (!contains<ComposedTree>(*elementRange, makeBoundaryPoint(end)))
1731 end = makeContainerOffsetPosition(elementRange->start);
1732 m_renderer->frame().selection().setSelection(VisibleSelection(start, end), FrameSelection::defaultSetSelectionOptions(UserTriggered));
1733 }
1734
1735 clearTextSelectionIntent(axObjectCache());
1736}

1796bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isSelected() const
1797{
1798 if (!m_renderer)
1799 return false;
1800
1801 if (!m_renderer->node())
1802 return false;
1803
1804 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(getAttribute(aria_selectedAttr), "true"))
1805 return true;
1806
1807 if (isTabItem() && isTabItemSelected())
1808 return true;
1809
1810 // Menu items are considered selectable by assistive technologies
1811 if (isMenuItem())
1812 return isFocused() || parentObjectUnignored()->activeDescendant() == this;
1813
1814 return false;
1815}
1816
1817bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isTabItemSelected() const
1818{
1819 if (!isTabItem() || !m_renderer)
1820 return false;
1821
1822 Node* node = m_renderer->node();
1823 if (!node || !node->isElementNode())
1824 return false;
1825
1826 // The ARIA spec says a tab item can also be selected if it is aria-labeled by a tabpanel
1827 // that has keyboard focus inside of it, or if a tabpanel in its aria-controls list has KB
1828 // focus inside of it.
1829 AccessibilityObject* focusedElement = static_cast<AccessibilityObject*>(focusedUIElement());
1830 if (!focusedElement)
1831 return false;
1832
1833 Vector<Element*> elements;
1834 elementsFromAttribute(elements, aria_controlsAttr);
1835
1836 AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache();
1837 if (!cache)
1838 return false;
1839
1840 for (const auto& element : elements) {
1841 AccessibilityObject* tabPanel = cache->getOrCreate(element);
1842
1843 // A tab item should only control tab panels.
1844 if (!tabPanel || tabPanel->roleValue() != AccessibilityRole::TabPanel)
1845 continue;
1846
1847 AccessibilityObject* checkFocusElement = focusedElement;
1848 // Check if the focused element is a descendant of the element controlled by the tab item.
1849 while (checkFocusElement) {
1850 if (tabPanel == checkFocusElement)
1851 return true;
1852 checkFocusElement = checkFocusElement->parentObject();
1853 }
1854 }
1855
1856 return false;
1857}
1858
1859bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isFocused() const
1860{
1861 if (!m_renderer)
1862 return false;
1863
1864 Document& document = m_renderer->document();
1865
1866 Element* focusedElement = document.focusedElement();
1867 if (!focusedElement)
1868 return false;
1869
1870 // A web area is represented by the Document node in the DOM tree, which isn't focusable.
1871 // Check instead if the frame's selection controller is focused
1872 if (focusedElement == m_renderer->node()
1873 || (roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::WebArea && document.frame()->selection().isFocusedAndActive()))
1874 return true;
1875
1876 return false;
1877}
1878
1879void AccessibilityRenderObject::setFocused(bool on)
1880{
1881 // Call the base class setFocused to ensure the view is focused and active.
1882 AccessibilityObject::setFocused(on);
1883
1884 if (!canSetFocusAttribute())
1885 return;
1886
1887 Document* document = this->document();
1888 Node* node = this->node();
1889
1890 if (!on || !is<Element>(node)) {
1891 document->setFocusedElement(nullptr);
1892 return;
1893 }
1894
1895 // When a node is told to set focus, that can cause it to be deallocated, which means that doing
1896 // anything else inside this object will crash. To fix this, we added a RefPtr to protect this object
1897 // long enough for duration.
1898 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> protectedThis(this);
1899
1900 // If this node is already the currently focused node, then calling focus() won't do anything.
1901 // That is a problem when focus is removed from the webpage to chrome, and then returns.
1902 // In these cases, we need to do what keyboard and mouse focus do, which is reset focus first.
1903 if (document->focusedElement() == node)
1904 document->setFocusedElement(nullptr);
1905
1906 // If we return from setFocusedElement and our element has been removed from a tree, axObjectCache() may be null.
1907 if (AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache()) {
1908 cache->setIsSynchronizingSelection(true);
1909 downcast<Element>(*node).focus();
1910 cache->setIsSynchronizingSelection(false);
1911 }
1912}
1913
1914void AccessibilityRenderObject::setSelectedRows(AccessibilityChildrenVector& selectedRows)
1915{
1916 // Setting selected only makes sense in trees and tables (and tree-tables).
1917 AccessibilityRole role = roleValue();
1918 if (role != AccessibilityRole::Tree && role != AccessibilityRole::TreeGrid && role != AccessibilityRole::Table && role != AccessibilityRole::Grid)
1919 return;
1920
1921 bool isMulti = isMultiSelectable();
1922 unsigned count = selectedRows.size();
1923 if (count > 1 && !isMulti)
1924 count = 1;
1925
1926 for (const auto& selectedRow : selectedRows)
1927 selectedRow->setSelected(true);
1928}
1929
1930bool AccessibilityRenderObject::setValue(const String& string)
1931{
1932 if (!m_renderer || !is<Element>(m_renderer->node()))
1933 return false;
1934
1935 Element& element = downcast<Element>(*m_renderer->node());
1936 RenderObject& renderer = *m_renderer;
1937
1938 // We should use the editor's insertText to mimic typing into the field.
1939 // Also only do this when the field is in editing mode.
1940 if (Frame* frame = renderer.document().frame()) {
1941 Editor& editor = frame->editor();
1942 if (element.shouldUseInputMethod()) {
1943 editor.clearText();
1944 editor.insertText(string, nullptr);
1945 return true;
1946 }
1947 }
1948 // FIXME: Do we want to do anything here for ARIA textboxes?
1949 if (renderer.isTextField() && is<HTMLInputElement>(element)) {
1950 downcast<HTMLInputElement>(element).setValue(string);
1951 return true;
1952 }
1953 if (renderer.isTextArea() && is<HTMLTextAreaElement>(element)) {
1954 downcast<HTMLTextAreaElement>(element).setValue(string);
1955 return true;
1956 }
1957
1958 return false;
1959}

1993AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::accessibilityParentForImageMap(HTMLMapElement* map) const
1994{
1995 // find an image that is using this map
1996 if (!map)
1997 return nullptr;

2008
2009AXCoreObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector AccessibilityRenderObject::documentLinks()
2010{
2011 AccessibilityChildrenVector result;
2012 Document& document = m_renderer->document();
2013 Ref<HTMLCollection> links = document.links();
2014 for (unsigned i = 0; auto* current = links->item(i); ++i) {
2015 if (auto* renderer = current->renderer()) {
2016 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> axObject = document.axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(renderer);
2017 ASSERT(axObject);
2018 if (!axObject->accessibilityIsIgnored() && axObject->isLink())
2019 result.append(axObject);
2020 } else {
2021 auto* parent = current->parentNode();
2022 if (is<HTMLAreaElement>(*current) && is<HTMLMapElement>(parent)) {
2023 auto& areaObject = downcast<AccessibilityImageMapLink>(*axObjectCache()->create(AccessibilityRole::ImageMapLink));
2024 HTMLMapElement& map = downcast<HTMLMapElement>(*parent);
2025 areaObject.setHTMLAreaElement(downcast<HTMLAreaElement>(current));
2026 areaObject.setHTMLMapElement(&map);
2027 areaObject.setParent(accessibilityParentForImageMap(&map));
2028
2029 result.append(&areaObject);
2030 }
2031 }
2032 }
2033
2034 return result;
2035}

2052
2053// This function is like a cross-platform version of - (WebCoreTextMarkerRange*)textMarkerRange. It returns
2054// a Range that we can convert to a WebCoreTextMarkerRange in the Obj-C file
2055VisiblePositionRange AccessibilityRenderObject::visiblePositionRange() const
2056{
2057 if (!m_renderer)
2058 return VisiblePositionRange();
2059
2060 Node* node = m_renderer->node();
2061 if (!node)
2062 return VisiblePositionRange();
2063
2064 VisiblePosition startPos = firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(node);
2065 VisiblePosition endPos = lastPositionInOrAfterNode(node);
2066
2067 // the VisiblePositions are equal for nodes like buttons, so adjust for that
2068 // FIXME: Really? [button, 0] and [button, 1] are distinct (before and after the button)
2069 // I expect this code is only hit for things like empty divs? In which case I don't think
2070 // the behavior is correct here -- eseidel
2071 if (startPos == endPos) {
2072 endPos = endPos.next();
2073 if (endPos.isNull())
2074 endPos = startPos;
2075 }
2076
2077 return { WTFMove(startPos), WTFMove(endPos) };
2078}
2079
2080VisiblePositionRange AccessibilityRenderObject::visiblePositionRangeForLine(unsigned lineCount) const
2081{
2082 if (!lineCount || !m_renderer)
2083 return VisiblePositionRange();
2084
2085 // iterate over the lines
2086 // FIXME: This is wrong when lineNumber is lineCount+1, because nextLinePosition takes you to the last offset of the last line.
2087 VisiblePosition position = m_renderer->view().positionForPoint(IntPoint(), nullptr);
2088 while (--lineCount) {
2089 auto previousLinePosition = position;
2090 position = nextLinePosition(position, 0);
2091 if (position.isNull() || position == previousLinePosition)
2092 return VisiblePositionRange();
2093 }
2094
2095 // make a caret selection for the marker position, then extend it to the line
2096 // NOTE: Ignores results of sel.modify because it returns false when starting at an empty line.
2097 // The resulting selection in that case will be a caret at position.
2098 FrameSelection selection;
2099 selection.setSelection(position);
2100 selection.modify(FrameSelection::AlterationExtend, SelectionDirection::Right, TextGranularity::LineBoundary);
2101 return selection.selection();
2102}
2103
2104VisiblePosition AccessibilityRenderObject::visiblePositionForIndex(int index) const
2105{
2106 if (!m_renderer)
2107 return VisiblePosition();
2108
2109 if (isNativeTextControl())

2182static IntRect boundsForRects(const LayoutRect& rect1, const LayoutRect& rect2, const SimpleRange& dataRange)
2183{
2184 LayoutRect ourRect = rect1;
2185 ourRect.unite(rect2);
2186
2187 // If the rectangle spans lines and contains multiple text characters, use the range's bounding box intead.
2188 if (rect1.maxY() != rect2.maxY() && characterCount(dataRange) > 1) {
2189 if (auto boundingBox = unionRect(RenderObject::absoluteTextRects(dataRange)); !boundingBox.isEmpty())
2190 ourRect = boundingBox;
2191 }
2192
2193 return snappedIntRect(ourRect);

2196IntRect AccessibilityRenderObject::boundsForVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePositionRange& visiblePositionRange) const
2197{
2198 if (visiblePositionRange.isNull())
2199 return IntRect();
2200
2201 // Create a mutable VisiblePositionRange.
2202 VisiblePositionRange range(visiblePositionRange);
2203 LayoutRect rect1 = range.start.absoluteCaretBounds();
2204 LayoutRect rect2 = range.end.absoluteCaretBounds();
2205
2206 // readjust for position at the edge of a line. This is to exclude line rect that doesn't need to be accounted in the range bounds
2207 if (rect2.y() != rect1.y()) {
2208 VisiblePosition endOfFirstLine = endOfLine(range.start);
2209 if (range.start == endOfFirstLine) {
2210 range.start.setAffinity(Affinity::Downstream);
2211 rect1 = range.start.absoluteCaretBounds();
2212 }
2213 if (range.end == endOfFirstLine) {
2214 range.end.setAffinity(Affinity::Upstream);
2215 rect2 = range.end.absoluteCaretBounds();
2216 }
2217 }
2218
2219 return boundsForRects(rect1, rect2, *makeSimpleRange(range));
2220}

2222IntRect AccessibilityRenderObject::boundsForRange(const SimpleRange& range) const
2223{
2224 auto cache = axObjectCache();
2225 if (!cache)
2226 return { };
2227
2228 auto start = cache->startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(range, true);
2229 auto end = cache->startOrEndCharacterOffsetForRange(range, false);
2230
2231 auto rect1 = cache->absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(start);
2232 auto rect2 = cache->absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(end);
2233
2234 // Readjust for position at the edge of a line. This is to exclude line rect that doesn't need to be accounted in the range bounds.
2235 if (rect2.y() != rect1.y()) {
2236 auto endOfFirstLine = cache->endCharacterOffsetOfLine(start);
2237 if (start.isEqual(endOfFirstLine)) {
2238 start = cache->nextCharacterOffset(start, false);
2239 rect1 = cache->absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(start);
2240 }
2241 if (end.isEqual(endOfFirstLine)) {
2242 end = cache->previousCharacterOffset(end, false);
2243 rect2 = cache->absoluteCaretBoundsForCharacterOffset(end);
2244 }
2245 }
2246
2247 return boundsForRects(rect1, rect2, range);
2248}

2267void AccessibilityRenderObject::setSelectedVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePositionRange& range) const
2268{
2269 if (range.isNull())
2270 return;
2271
2272 // In WebKit1, when the top web area sets the selection to be an input element in an iframe, the caret will disappear.
2273 // FrameSelection::setSelectionWithoutUpdatingAppearance is setting the selection on the new frame in this case, and causing this behavior.
2274 if (isWebArea() && parentObject() && parentObject()->isAttachment()
2275 && isVisiblePositionRangeInDifferentDocument(range))
2276 return;
2277
2278 // make selection and tell the document to use it. if it's zero length, then move to that position
2279 if (range.start == range.end) {
2280 setTextSelectionIntent(axObjectCache(), AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionMove);
2281
2282 auto start = range.start;
2283 if (auto elementRange = this->elementRange()) {
2284 if (!contains<ComposedTree>(*elementRange, makeBoundaryPoint(start)))
2285 start = makeContainerOffsetPosition(elementRange->start);
2286 }
2287
2288 m_renderer->frame().selection().moveTo(start, UserTriggered);
2289 } else {
2290 setTextSelectionIntent(axObjectCache(), AXTextStateChangeTypeSelectionExtend);
2291
2292 VisibleSelection newSelection = VisibleSelection(range.start, range.end);
2293 m_renderer->frame().selection().setSelection(newSelection, FrameSelection::defaultSetSelectionOptions());
2294 }
2295
2296 clearTextSelectionIntent(axObjectCache());

2299VisiblePosition AccessibilityRenderObject::visiblePositionForPoint(const IntPoint& point) const
2300{
2301 if (!m_renderer)
2302 return VisiblePosition();
2303
2304 // convert absolute point to view coordinates
2305 RenderView* renderView = topRenderer();
2306 if (!renderView)
2307 return VisiblePosition();
2308
2309#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
2310 FrameView* frameView = &renderView->frameView();
2311#endif
2312
2313 Node* innerNode = nullptr;
2314
2315 // Locate the node containing the point
2316 // FIXME: Remove this loop and instead add HitTestRequest::Type::AllowVisibleChildFrameContentOnly to the hit test request type.
2317 LayoutPoint pointResult;
2318 while (1) {
2319 LayoutPoint pointToUse;
2320#if PLATFORM(MAC)
2321 pointToUse = frameView->screenToContents(point);
2322#else
2323 pointToUse = point;
2324#endif
2325 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::Active };
2326 HitTestResult result { pointToUse };
2327 renderView->document().hitTest(hitType, result);
2328 innerNode = result.innerNode();
2329 if (!innerNode)
2330 return VisiblePosition();
2331
2332 RenderObject* renderer = innerNode->renderer();
2333 if (!renderer)
2334 return VisiblePosition();
2335
2336 pointResult = result.localPoint();
2337
2338 // done if hit something other than a widget
2339 if (!is<RenderWidget>(*renderer))
2340 break;
2341
2342 // descend into widget (FRAME, IFRAME, OBJECT...)
2343 Widget* widget = downcast<RenderWidget>(*renderer).widget();
2344 if (!is<FrameView>(widget))
2345 break;
2346 Frame& frame = downcast<FrameView>(*widget).frame();
2347 renderView = frame.document()->renderView();
2348#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
2349 frameView = downcast<FrameView>(widget);
2350#endif
2351 }
2352
2353 return innerNode->renderer()->positionForPoint(pointResult, nullptr);
2354}

2384void AccessibilityRenderObject::lineBreaks(Vector<int>& lineBreaks) const
2385{
2386 if (!isTextControl())
2387 return;
2388
2389 VisiblePosition visiblePos = visiblePositionForIndex(0);
2390 VisiblePosition savedVisiblePos = visiblePos;
2391 visiblePos = nextLinePosition(visiblePos, 0);
2392 while (!visiblePos.isNull() && visiblePos != savedVisiblePos) {
2393 lineBreaks.append(indexForVisiblePosition(visiblePos));
2394 savedVisiblePos = visiblePos;
2395 visiblePos = nextLinePosition(visiblePos, 0);
2396 }
2397}

2399// Given a line number, the range of characters of the text associated with this accessibility
2400// object that contains the line number.
2401PlainTextRange AccessibilityRenderObject::doAXRangeForLine(unsigned lineNumber) const
2402{
2403 if (!isTextControl())
2404 return PlainTextRange();
2405
2406 // iterate to the specified line
2407 VisiblePosition visiblePos = visiblePositionForIndex(0);
2408 VisiblePosition savedVisiblePos;
2409 for (unsigned lineCount = lineNumber; lineCount; lineCount -= 1) {
2410 savedVisiblePos = visiblePos;
2411 visiblePos = nextLinePosition(visiblePos, 0);
2412 if (visiblePos.isNull() || visiblePos == savedVisiblePos)
2413 return PlainTextRange();
2414 }
2415
2416 // Get the end of the line based on the starting position.
2417 VisiblePosition endPosition = endOfLine(visiblePos);
2418
2419 int index1 = indexForVisiblePosition(visiblePos);
2420 int index2 = indexForVisiblePosition(endPosition);
2421
2422 // add one to the end index for a line break not caused by soft line wrap (to match AppKit)
2423 if (endPosition.affinity() == Affinity::Downstream && endPosition.next().isNotNull())
2424 index2 += 1;
2425
2426 // return nil rather than an zero-length range (to match AppKit)
2427 if (index1 == index2)
2428 return PlainTextRange();
2429
2430 return PlainTextRange(index1, index2 - index1);
2431}
2432
2433// The composed character range in the text associated with this accessibility object that
2434// is specified by the given index value. This parameterized attribute returns the complete
2435// range of characters (including surrogate pairs of multi-byte glyphs) at the given index.
2436PlainTextRange AccessibilityRenderObject::doAXRangeForIndex(unsigned index) const
2437{
2438 if (!isTextControl())
2439 return PlainTextRange();
2440
2441 String elementText = text();
2442 if (!elementText.length() || index > elementText.length() - 1)
2443 return PlainTextRange();
2444
2445 return PlainTextRange(index, 1);
2446}

2448// A substring of the text associated with this accessibility object that is

2450String AccessibilityRenderObject::doAXStringForRange(const PlainTextRange& range) const

2453 return String();
2454
2455 if (!isTextControl())
2456 return String();
2457
2458 String elementText = isPasswordField() ? passwordFieldValue() : text();
2459 return elementText.substring(range.start, range.length);
2460}

2526
2527AXCoreObject* AccessibilityRenderObject::accessibilityHitTest(const IntPoint& point) const
2528{
2529 if (!m_renderer || !m_renderer->hasLayer())
2530 return nullptr;
2531
2532 m_renderer->document().updateLayout();
2533
2534 if (!m_renderer || !m_renderer->hasLayer())
2535 return nullptr;
2536
2537 RenderLayer* layer = downcast<RenderBox>(*m_renderer).layer();
2538
2539 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::AccessibilityHitTest };
2540 HitTestResult hitTestResult { point };
2541 layer->hitTest(hitType, hitTestResult);
2542 Node* node = hitTestResult.innerNode();
2543 if (!node)
2544 return nullptr;
2545 Node* shadowAncestorNode = node->shadowHost();
2546 if (shouldUseShadowHostForHitTesting(shadowAncestorNode))
2547 node = shadowAncestorNode;
2548 ASSERT(node);
2549
2550 if (is<HTMLAreaElement>(*node))
2551 return accessibilityImageMapHitTest(downcast<HTMLAreaElement>(node), point);
2552
2553 if (is<HTMLOptionElement>(*node))
2554 node = downcast<HTMLOptionElement>(*node).ownerSelectElement();
2555
2556 RenderObject* obj = node->renderer();
2557 if (!obj)
2558 return nullptr;
2559
2560 AXCoreObject* result = obj->document().axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(obj);
2561 result->updateChildrenIfNecessary();
2562
2563 // Allow the element to perform any hit-testing it might need to do to reach non-render children.
2564 result = static_cast<AccessibilityObject*>(result->elementAccessibilityHitTest(point));
2565
2566 if (result && result->accessibilityIsIgnored()) {
2567 // If this element is the label of a control, a hit test should return the control.
2568 auto* controlObject = result->correspondingControlForLabelElement();
2569 if (controlObject && !controlObject->titleUIElement())
2570 return controlObject;
2571
2572 result = result->parentObjectUnignored();
2573 }
2574
2575 return result;
2576}

2661{
2662 Element* element = downcast<Element>(renderer()->node());
2663 if (!element)
2664 return;
2665 if (!renderer()->frame().selection().isFocusedAndActive() || renderer()->document().focusedElement() != element)
2666 return;

2669 if (activeDescendant && shouldNotifyActiveDescendant()) {
2670 auto* targetRenderer = renderer();
2671
2672#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
2673 // If the combobox's activeDescendant is inside another object, the target element should be that parent.
2674 if (isComboBox()) {
2675 if (auto* ariaOwner = targetElementForActiveDescendant(aria_ownsAttr, activeDescendant))
2676 targetRenderer = ariaOwner;
2677 else if (auto* ariaController = targetElementForActiveDescendant(aria_controlsAttr, activeDescendant))
2678 targetRenderer = ariaController;
2679 }
2680#endif
2681
2682 renderer()->document().axObjectCache()->postNotification(targetRenderer, AXObjectCache::AXActiveDescendantChanged);
2683 }

2723{

2725 if (is<RenderTextControl>(renderer))

2738 return true;

2802AccessibilityRole AccessibilityRenderObject::determineAccessibilityRole()
2803{
2804 AXTRACE("AccessibilityRenderObject::determineAccessibilityRole");
2805 if (!m_renderer)
2806 return AccessibilityRole::Unknown;
2807
2808#if ENABLE(APPLE_PAY)
2809 if (isApplePayButton())
2810 return AccessibilityRole::Button;
