2812
2813 // Sometimes we need to ignore the attribute role. Like if a tree is malformed,
2814 // we want to ignore the treeitem's attribute role.
2815 if ((m_ariaRole = determineAriaRoleAttribute()) != AccessibilityRole::Unknown && !shouldIgnoreAttributeRole())
2816 return m_ariaRole;
2817
2818 Node* node = m_renderer->node();
2819 RenderBoxModelObject* cssBox = renderBoxModelObject();
2820
2821 if (node && node->isLink())
2822 return AccessibilityRole::WebCoreLink;
2823 if (node && is<HTMLImageElement>(*node) && downcast<HTMLImageElement>(*node).hasAttributeWithoutSynchronization(usemapAttr))
2824 return AccessibilityRole::ImageMap;
2825 if ((cssBox && cssBox->isListItem()) || (node && node->hasTagName(liTag)))
2826 return AccessibilityRole::ListItem;
2827 if (m_renderer->isListMarker())
2828 return AccessibilityRole::ListMarker;
2829 if (node && node->hasTagName(buttonTag))
2830 return buttonRoleType();
2831 if (node && node->hasTagName(legendTag))
2832 return AccessibilityRole::Legend;
2833 if (m_renderer->isText())
2834 return AccessibilityRole::StaticText;
2835 if (cssBox && cssBox->isImage()) {
2836 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(node))
2837 return hasPopup() ? AccessibilityRole::PopUpButton : AccessibilityRole::Button;
2838
2839 if (auto* svgRoot = remoteSVGRootElement(Create)) {
2840 if (svgRoot->hasAccessibleContent())
2841 return AccessibilityRole::SVGRoot;
2842 }
2843
2844 return AccessibilityRole::Image;
2845 }
2846
2847 if (node && node->hasTagName(canvasTag))
2848 return AccessibilityRole::Canvas;
2849
2850 if (cssBox && cssBox->isRenderView())
2851 return AccessibilityRole::WebArea;
2852
2853 if (cssBox && cssBox->isTextField()) {
2854 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(node))
2855 return downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*node).isSearchField() ? AccessibilityRole::SearchField : AccessibilityRole::TextField;
2856 }
2857
2858 if (cssBox && cssBox->isTextArea())
2859 return AccessibilityRole::TextArea;
2860
2861 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(node)) {
2862 HTMLInputElement& input = downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*node);
2863 if (input.isCheckbox())
2864 return AccessibilityRole::CheckBox;
2865 if (input.isRadioButton())
2866 return AccessibilityRole::RadioButton;
2867 if (input.isTextButton())
2868 return buttonRoleType();
2869 // On iOS, the date field and time field are popup buttons. On other platforms they are text fields.
2870#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2871 if (input.isDateField() || input.isTimeField())
2872 return AccessibilityRole::PopUpButton;
2873#endif
2874#if ENABLE(INPUT_TYPE_COLOR)
2875 if (input.isColorControl())
2876 return AccessibilityRole::ColorWell;
2877#endif
2878 }
2879
2880 if (hasContentEditableAttributeSet())
2881 return AccessibilityRole::TextArea;
2882
2883 if (isFileUploadButton())
2884 return AccessibilityRole::Button;
2885
2886 if (cssBox && cssBox->isMenuList())
2887 return AccessibilityRole::PopUpButton;
2888
2889 if (headingLevel())
2890 return AccessibilityRole::Heading;
2891
2892 if (m_renderer->isSVGRoot())
2893 return AccessibilityRole::SVGRoot;
2894
2895 if (isStyleFormatGroup()) {
2896 if (node->hasTagName(delTag))
2897 return AccessibilityRole::Deletion;
2898 if (node->hasTagName(insTag))
2899 return AccessibilityRole::Insertion;
2900 if (node->hasTagName(subTag))
2901 return AccessibilityRole::Subscript;
2902 if (node->hasTagName(supTag))
2903 return AccessibilityRole::Superscript;
2904 return is<RenderInline>(*m_renderer) ? AccessibilityRole::Inline : AccessibilityRole::TextGroup;
2905 }
2906
2907 if (node && node->hasTagName(ddTag))
2908 return AccessibilityRole::DescriptionListDetail;
2909
2910 if (node && node->hasTagName(dtTag))
2911 return AccessibilityRole::DescriptionListTerm;
2912
2913 if (node && node->hasTagName(dlTag))
2914 return AccessibilityRole::DescriptionList;
2915
2916 if (node && node->hasTagName(fieldsetTag))
2917 return AccessibilityRole::Group;
2918
2919 if (node && node->hasTagName(figureTag))
2920 return AccessibilityRole::Figure;
2921
2922 // Check for Ruby elements
2923 if (m_renderer->isRubyText())
2924 return AccessibilityRole::RubyText;
2925 if (m_renderer->isRubyBase())
2926 return AccessibilityRole::RubyBase;
2927 if (m_renderer->isRubyRun())
2928 return AccessibilityRole::RubyRun;
2929 if (m_renderer->isRubyBlock())
2930 return AccessibilityRole::RubyBlock;
2931 if (m_renderer->isRubyInline())
2932 return AccessibilityRole::RubyInline;
2933
2934 // This return value is what will be used if AccessibilityTableCell determines
2935 // the cell should not be treated as a cell (e.g. because it is a layout table.
2936 if (is<RenderTableCell>(renderer()))
2937 return AccessibilityRole::TextGroup;
2938
2939 // Table sections should be ignored.
2940 if (m_renderer->isTableSection())
2941 return AccessibilityRole::Ignored;
2942
2943 if (m_renderer->isHR())
2944 return AccessibilityRole::HorizontalRule;
2945
2946 if (node && node->hasTagName(pTag))
2947 return AccessibilityRole::Paragraph;
2948
2949 if (is<HTMLLabelElement>(node))
2950 return AccessibilityRole::Label;
2951
2952 if (node && node->hasTagName(dfnTag))
2953 return AccessibilityRole::Definition;
2954
2955 if (node && node->hasTagName(divTag))
2956 return AccessibilityRole::Div;
2957
2958 if (is<HTMLFormElement>(node))
2959 return AccessibilityRole::Form;
2960
2961 if (node && node->hasTagName(articleTag))
2962 return AccessibilityRole::DocumentArticle;
2963
2964 if (node && node->hasTagName(mainTag))
2965 return AccessibilityRole::LandmarkMain;
2966
2967 if (node && node->hasTagName(navTag))
2968 return AccessibilityRole::LandmarkNavigation;
2969
2970 if (node && node->hasTagName(asideTag))
2971 return AccessibilityRole::LandmarkComplementary;
2972
2973 // The default role attribute value for the section element, region, became a landmark in ARIA 1.1.
2974 // The HTML AAM spec says it is "strongly recommended" that ATs only convey and provide navigation
2975 // for section elements which have names.
2976 if (node && node->hasTagName(sectionTag))
2977 return hasAttribute(aria_labelAttr) || hasAttribute(aria_labelledbyAttr) ? AccessibilityRole::LandmarkRegion : AccessibilityRole::TextGroup;
2978
2979 if (node && node->hasTagName(addressTag))
2980 return AccessibilityRole::Group;
2981
2982 if (node && node->hasTagName(blockquoteTag))
2983 return AccessibilityRole::Blockquote;
2984
2985 if (node && node->hasTagName(captionTag))
2986 return AccessibilityRole::Caption;
2987
2988 if (node && node->hasTagName(markTag))
2989 return AccessibilityRole::Mark;
2990
2991 if (node && node->hasTagName(preTag))
2992 return AccessibilityRole::Pre;
2993
2994 if (is<HTMLDetailsElement>(node))
2995 return AccessibilityRole::Details;
2996 if (is<HTMLSummaryElement>(node))
2997 return AccessibilityRole::Summary;
2998
2999 // http://rawgit.com/w3c/aria/master/html-aam/html-aam.html
3000 // Output elements should be mapped to status role.
3001 if (isOutput())
3002 return AccessibilityRole::ApplicationStatus;
3003
3004#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
3005 if (is<HTMLVideoElement>(node))
3006 return AccessibilityRole::Video;
3007 if (is<HTMLAudioElement>(node))
3008 return AccessibilityRole::Audio;
3009#endif
3010
3011 // The HTML element should not be exposed as an element. That's what the RenderView element does.
3012 if (node && node->hasTagName(htmlTag))
3013 return AccessibilityRole::Ignored;
3014

3016 // then it should not be exposed as whole page's banner/contentInfo
3017 if (node && node->hasTagName(headerTag) && !isDescendantOfElementType({ articleTag, sectionTag }))
3018 return AccessibilityRole::LandmarkBanner;
3019
3020 // http://webkit.org/b/190138 Footers should become contentInfo's if scoped to body (and consequently become a landmark).
3021 // It should remain a footer if scoped to main, sectioning elements (article, section) or root sectioning element (blockquote, details, dialog, fieldset, figure, td).
3022 if (node && node->hasTagName(footerTag)) {
3023 if (!isDescendantOfElementType({ articleTag, sectionTag, mainTag, blockquoteTag, detailsTag, fieldsetTag, figureTag, tdTag }))
3024 return AccessibilityRole::LandmarkContentInfo;
3025 return AccessibilityRole::Footer;
3026 }
3027
3028 // menu tags with toolbar type should have Toolbar role.
3029 if (node && node->hasTagName(menuTag) && equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(getAttribute(typeAttr), "toolbar"))
3030 return AccessibilityRole::Toolbar;
3031
3032 if (node && node->hasTagName(timeTag))
3033 return AccessibilityRole::Time;
3034
3035 // If the element does not have role, but it has ARIA attributes, or accepts tab focus, accessibility should fallback to exposing it as a group.
3036 if (supportsARIAAttributes() || canSetFocusAttribute())
3037 return AccessibilityRole::Group;
3038
3039 if (m_renderer->isRenderBlockFlow())
3040 return m_renderer->isAnonymousBlock() ? AccessibilityRole::TextGroup : AccessibilityRole::Group;
3041
3042 // InlineRole is the final fallback before assigning AccessibilityRole::Unknown to an object. It makes it
3043 // possible to distinguish truly unknown objects from non-focusable inline text elements
3044 // which have an event handler or attribute suggesting possible inclusion by the platform.
3045 if (is<RenderInline>(*m_renderer)
3046 && (hasAttributesRequiredForInclusion()
3047 || (node && node->hasEventListeners())
3048 || (supportsDatetimeAttribute() && !getAttribute(datetimeAttr).isEmpty())))
3049 return AccessibilityRole::Inline;
3050
3051 return AccessibilityRole::Unknown;
3052}

3054AccessibilityOrientation AccessibilityRenderObject::orientation() const
3055{
3056 const AtomString& ariaOrientation = getAttribute(aria_orientationAttr);
3057 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaOrientation, "horizontal"))
3058 return AccessibilityOrientation::Horizontal;
3059 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaOrientation, "vertical"))
3060 return AccessibilityOrientation::Vertical;
3061 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaOrientation, "undefined"))
3062 return AccessibilityOrientation::Undefined;
3063
3064 // In ARIA 1.1, the implicit value of aria-orientation changed from horizontal
3065 // to undefined on all roles that don't have their own role-specific values. In
3066 // addition, the implicit value of combobox became undefined.
3067 if (isComboBox() || isRadioGroup() || isTreeGrid())
3068 return AccessibilityOrientation::Undefined;
3069
3070 if (isScrollbar() || isListBox() || isMenu() || isTree())
3071 return AccessibilityOrientation::Vertical;
3072
3073 if (isMenuBar() || isSplitter() || isTabList() || isToolbar() || isSlider())
3074 return AccessibilityOrientation::Horizontal;
3075
3076 return AccessibilityObject::orientation();
3077}

3079bool AccessibilityRenderObject::inheritsPresentationalRole() const
3080{
3081 // ARIA states if an item can get focus, it should not be presentational.
3082 if (canSetFocusAttribute())
3083 return false;
3084
3085 // ARIA spec says that when a parent object is presentational, and it has required child elements,
3086 // those child elements are also presentational. For example, <li> becomes presentational from <ul>.
3087 // http://www.w3.org/WAI/PF/aria/complete#presentation
3088
3089 const Vector<const HTMLQualifiedName*>* parentTags;
3090 switch (roleValue()) {
3091 case AccessibilityRole::ListItem:
3092 case AccessibilityRole::ListMarker: {
3093 static const auto listItemParents = makeNeverDestroyed(Vector<const HTMLQualifiedName*> { &dlTag.get(), &olTag.get(), &ulTag.get() });
3094 parentTags = &listItemParents.get();
3095 break;
3096 }
3097 case AccessibilityRole::GridCell:
3098 case AccessibilityRole::Cell: {
3099 static const auto tableCellParents = makeNeverDestroyed(Vector<const HTMLQualifiedName*> { &tableTag.get() });
3100 parentTags = &tableCellParents.get();
3101 break;
3102 }
3103 default:
3104 // Not all elements need to do the following check, only ones that are required children.
3105 return false;
3106 }
3107
3108 for (auto* parent = parentObject(); parent; parent = parent->parentObject()) {
3109 if (!is<AccessibilityRenderObject>(*parent))
3110 continue;
3111
3112 Node* node = downcast<AccessibilityRenderObject>(*parent).node();
3113 if (!is<Element>(node))
3114 continue;
3115
3116 // If native tag of the parent element matches an acceptable name, then return
3117 // based on its presentational status.
3118 auto& name = downcast<Element>(*node).tagQName();
3119 if (std::any_of(parentTags->begin(), parentTags->end(), [&name] (auto* possibleName) { return *possibleName == name; }))
3120 return parent->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::Presentational;
3121 }
3122
3123 return false;
3124}
3125
3126bool AccessibilityRenderObject::isPresentationalChildOfAriaRole() const
3127{
3128 // Walk the parent chain looking for a parent that has presentational children
3129 AccessibilityObject* parent;
3130 for (parent = parentObject(); parent && !parent->ariaRoleHasPresentationalChildren(); parent = parent->parentObject())
3131 { }
3132
3133 return parent;
3134}

3139 case AccessibilityRole::Button:
3140 case AccessibilityRole::Slider:
3141 case AccessibilityRole::Image:
3142 case AccessibilityRole::ProgressIndicator:
3143 case AccessibilityRole::SpinButton:
3144 // case SeparatorRole:
3145 return true;
3146 default:
3147 return false;

3240AccessibilitySVGRoot* AccessibilityRenderObject::remoteSVGRootElement(CreationChoice createIfNecessary) const
3241{
3242 if (!is<RenderImage>(renderer()))
3243 return nullptr;
3244
3245 CachedImage* cachedImage = downcast<RenderImage>(*m_renderer).cachedImage();
3246 if (!cachedImage)
3247 return nullptr;
3248
3249 Image* image = cachedImage->image();
3250 if (!is<SVGImage>(image))
3251 return nullptr;
3252
3253 FrameView* frameView = downcast<SVGImage>(*image).frameView();
3254 if (!frameView)
3255 return nullptr;
3256 Frame& frame = frameView->frame();
3257
3258 Document* document = frame.document();
3259 if (!is<SVGDocument>(document))
3260 return nullptr;
3261
3262 auto rootElement = DocumentSVG::rootElement(*document);
3263 if (!rootElement)
3264 return nullptr;
3265 RenderObject* rendererRoot = rootElement->renderer();
3266 if (!rendererRoot)
3267 return nullptr;
3268
3269 AXObjectCache* cache = frame.document()->axObjectCache();
3270 if (!cache)
3271 return nullptr;
3272 AccessibilityObject* rootSVGObject = createIfNecessary == Create ? cache->getOrCreate(rendererRoot) : cache->get(rendererRoot);
3273
3274 ASSERT(!createIfNecessary || rootSVGObject);
3275 if (!is<AccessibilitySVGRoot>(rootSVGObject))
3276 return nullptr;
3277
3278 return downcast<AccessibilitySVGRoot>(rootSVGObject);
3279}

3340// Hidden children are those that are not rendered or visible, but are specifically marked as aria-hidden=false,
3341// meaning that they should be exposed to the AX hierarchy.
3342void AccessibilityRenderObject::addHiddenChildren()
3343{
3344 Node* node = this->node();
3345 if (!node)
3346 return;
3347
3348 // First do a quick run through to determine if we have any hidden nodes (most often we will not).
3349 // If we do have hidden nodes, we need to determine where to insert them so they match DOM order as close as possible.
3350 bool shouldInsertHiddenNodes = false;
3351 for (Node* child = node->firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
3352 if (!child->renderer() && isNodeAriaVisible(child)) {
3353 shouldInsertHiddenNodes = true;
3354 break;
3355 }
3356 }
3357
3358 if (!shouldInsertHiddenNodes)
3359 return;
3360
3361 // Iterate through all of the children, including those that may have already been added, and
3362 // try to insert hidden nodes in the correct place in the DOM order.
3363 unsigned insertionIndex = 0;
3364 for (Node* child = node->firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
3365 if (child->renderer()) {
3366 // Find out where the last render sibling is located within m_children.
3367 AXCoreObject* childObject = axObjectCache()->get(child->renderer());
3368 if (childObject && childObject->accessibilityIsIgnored()) {
3369 auto& children = childObject->children();
3370 if (children.size())
3371 childObject = children.last().get();
3372 else
3373 childObject = nullptr;
3374 }
3375
3376 if (childObject)
3377 insertionIndex = m_children.find(childObject) + 1;
3378 continue;
3379 }
3380
3381 if (!isNodeAriaVisible(child))
3382 continue;
3383
3384 unsigned previousSize = m_children.size();
3385 if (insertionIndex > previousSize)
3386 insertionIndex = previousSize;
3387
3388 insertChild(axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(child), insertionIndex);
3389 insertionIndex += (m_children.size() - previousSize);
3390 }
3391}

3393void AccessibilityRenderObject::updateRoleAfterChildrenCreation()
3394{
3395 AXTRACE("AccessibilityRenderObject::updateRoleAfterChildrenCreation");
3396 // If a menu does not have valid menuitem children, it should not be exposed as a menu.
3397 auto role = roleValue();
3398 if (role == AccessibilityRole::Menu) {
3399 // Elements marked as menus must have at least one menu item child.
3400 size_t menuItemCount = 0;
3401 for (const auto& child : children()) {
3402 if (child->isMenuItem()) {
3403 menuItemCount++;
3404 break;
3405 }
3406 }
3407
3408 if (!menuItemCount)
3409 m_role = AccessibilityRole::Group;
3410 }
3411 if (role == AccessibilityRole::SVGRoot && !hasChildren())
3412 m_role = AccessibilityRole::Image;
3413}

3415void AccessibilityRenderObject::addChildren()
3416{
3417 // If the need to add more children in addition to existing children arises,
3418 // childrenChanged should have been called, leaving the object with no children.
3419 ASSERT(!m_haveChildren);
3420
3421 m_haveChildren = true;
3422
3423 if (!canHaveChildren())
3424 return;
3425
3426 for (RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> obj = firstChild(); obj; obj = obj->nextSibling())
3427 addChild(obj.get());
3428
3429 m_subtreeDirty = false;
3430
3431 addHiddenChildren();
3432 addAttachmentChildren();
3433 addImageMapChildren();
3434 addTextFieldChildren();
3435 addCanvasChildren();
3436 addRemoteSVGChildren();
3437
3438#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
3439 updateAttachmentViewParents();
3440#endif
3441
3442 updateRoleAfterChildrenCreation();
3443}

3494{

3498bool AccessibilityRenderObject::canHaveSelectedChildren() const
3499{
3500 switch (roleValue()) {
3501 // These roles are containers whose children support aria-selected:
3502 case AccessibilityRole::Grid:
3503 case AccessibilityRole::ListBox:
3504 case AccessibilityRole::TabList:
3505 case AccessibilityRole::Tree:
3506 case AccessibilityRole::TreeGrid:
3507 case AccessibilityRole::List:
3508 // These roles are containers whose children are treated as selected by assistive
3509 // technologies. We can get the "selected" item via aria-activedescendant or the
3510 // focused element.
3511 case AccessibilityRole::Menu:
3512 case AccessibilityRole::MenuBar:
3513 return true;
3514 default:
3515 return false;
3516 }
3517}
3518
3519void AccessibilityRenderObject::ariaSelectedRows(AccessibilityChildrenVector& result)
3520{
3521 // Determine which rows are selected.
3522 bool isMulti = isMultiSelectable();
3523
3524 // Prefer active descendant over aria-selected.
3525 AccessibilityObject* activeDesc = activeDescendant();
3526 if (activeDesc && (activeDesc->isTreeItem() || activeDesc->isTableRow())) {
3527 result.append(activeDesc);
3528 if (!isMulti)
3529 return;
3530 }
3531
3532 // Get all the rows.
3533 auto rowsIteration = [&](const auto& rows) {
3534 for (auto& row : rows) {
3535 if (row->isSelected() || row->isActiveDescendantOfFocusedContainer()) {
3536 result.append(row);
3537 if (!isMulti)
3538 break;
3539 }
3540 }
3541 };
3542 if (isTree()) {
3543 AccessibilityChildrenVector allRows;
3544 ariaTreeRows(allRows);
3545 rowsIteration(allRows);
3546 } else if (is<AccessibilityTable>(*this)) {
3547 auto& thisTable = downcast<AccessibilityTable>(*this);
3548 if (thisTable.isExposable() && thisTable.supportsSelectedRows())
3549 rowsIteration(thisTable.rows());
3550 }
3551}
3552
3553void AccessibilityRenderObject::ariaListboxSelectedChildren(AccessibilityChildrenVector& result)
3554{
3555 bool isMulti = isMultiSelectable();
3556
3557 for (const auto& child : children()) {
3558 // Every child should have aria-role option, and if so, check for selected attribute/state.
3559 if (child->ariaRoleAttribute() == AccessibilityRole::ListBoxOption && (child->isSelected() || child->isActiveDescendantOfFocusedContainer())) {
3560 result.append(child);
3561 if (!isMulti)
3562 return;
3563 }
3564 }
3565}
3566
3567void AccessibilityRenderObject::selectedChildren(AccessibilityChildrenVector& result)
3568{
3569 ASSERT(result.isEmpty());
3570
3571 if (!canHaveSelectedChildren())
3572 return;
3573
3574 switch (roleValue()) {
3575 case AccessibilityRole::ListBox:
3576 // native list boxes would be AccessibilityListBoxes, so only check for aria list boxes
3577 ariaListboxSelectedChildren(result);
3578 return;
3579 case AccessibilityRole::Grid:
3580 case AccessibilityRole::Tree:
3581 case AccessibilityRole::TreeGrid:
3582 ariaSelectedRows(result);
3583 return;
3584 case AccessibilityRole::TabList:
3585 if (AXCoreObject* selectedTab = selectedTabItem())
3586 result.append(selectedTab);
3587 return;
3588 case AccessibilityRole::List:
3589 if (auto* selectedListItemChild = selectedListItem())
3590 result.append(selectedListItemChild);
3591 return;
3592 case AccessibilityRole::Menu:
3593 case AccessibilityRole::MenuBar:
3594 if (AccessibilityObject* descendant = activeDescendant()) {
3595 result.append(descendant);
3596 return;
3597 }
3598 if (AccessibilityObject* focusedElement = static_cast<AccessibilityObject*>(focusedUIElement())) {
3599 result.append(focusedElement);
3600 return;
3601 }
3602 return;
3603 default:
3604 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3605 }
3606}

3900String AccessibilityRenderObject::passwordFieldValue() const
3901{
3902 ASSERT(isPasswordField());
3903
3904 // Look for the RenderText object in the RenderObject tree for this input field.
3905 RenderObject* renderer = node()->renderer();
3906 while (renderer && !is<RenderText>(renderer))
3907 renderer = downcast<RenderElement>(*renderer).firstChild();
3908
3909 if (!is<RenderText>(renderer))
3910 return String();
3911
3912 // Return the text that is actually being rendered in the input field.
3913 return downcast<RenderText>(*renderer).textWithoutConvertingBackslashToYenSymbol();

3916ScrollableArea* AccessibilityRenderObject::getScrollableAreaIfScrollable() const
3917{
3918 // If the parent is a scroll view, then this object isn't really scrollable, the parent ScrollView should handle the scrolling.
3919 if (auto* parent = parentObject()) {
3920 if (parent->isScrollView())
3921 return nullptr;
3922 }
3923
3924 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer()))
3925 return nullptr;
3926
3927 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(*m_renderer);
3928 if (!box.canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea())
3929 return nullptr;
3930
3931 return box.layer() ? box.layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr;
3932}

3934void AccessibilityRenderObject::scrollTo(const IntPoint& point) const
3935{
3936 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer()))
3937 return;
3938
3939 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(*m_renderer);
3940 if (!box.canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea())
3941 return;

3943 // FIXME: is point a ScrollOffset or ScrollPosition? Test in RTL overflow.
3944 ASSERT(box.layer());
3945 ASSERT(box.layer()->scrollableArea());
3946 box.layer()->scrollableArea()->scrollToOffset(point);
3947}
